	WireMock Test Scenario: NOTPERMIT with Empty Records Element
	
	This file simulates a CICS CMCI response where the user has NO authorization
	to view a specific resource type (e.g., PROGRAM).
	
	Error Details:
	- api_response1: 1031 (NOTPERMIT) - User lacks permissions
	- api_response2: 1345 (USRID) - User ID related authorization issue
	- api_response1_alt: "NOTPERMIT"
	- api_response2_alt: "USRID"
	
	Scenario:
	The NOTPERMIT error is returned with an EMPTY <records> element (not missing).
	This represents a scenario where the user tries to expand a resource type
	(e.g., Programs tab) but has no authorization to view that resource type.
	
	Key Difference from Other Scenarios:
	- MYPLEX3: NOTPERMIT with records present → SDK accepts, partialResults=true
	- MYPLEX4: NOTPERMIT with NO <records> element → SDK throws error
	- THIS: NOTPERMIT with EMPTY <records> element → SDK throws error
	
	Expected Behavior:
	The SDK should throw an error because the records object is empty (no keys).
	This is treated the same as having no records element at all.
	
	Related Code:
	- packages/sdk/src/rest/CicsCmciRestClient.ts (verifyResponseCodes method)
	- Object.keys(apiResponse.response.records).length > 0 check
	
	SDK Logic:
	if (apiResponse.response?.records && Object.keys(apiResponse.response.records).length > 0) {
	  // This condition is NOT met when records is empty {}
	  return apiResponse;
	}
	// Falls through to error handling
	throw new ImperativeError(...);
